Norwegian state oil company Den NorskeStats Oljeselskap (Statoil) signed contracts worth a total of1.5 billion Norwegian crowns in connection with the developmentof the Veslefrikk oil field, Statoil said.    Moss Rosenberg Verft of Stavanger has been awarded acontract to convert the the drilling platform West Vision to afloating production platform. The work is to be completed inthe summer of 1989.    Aker Verdal has been awarded a contract for theengineering, purchasing and construction of the steel jacketfor the wellhead platform, also to be completed in 1989,Statoil said. Reuter&#3;